Gender Pay Gap Report 2017 

 
 
 
Leeds City College prides itself on being an inclusive employer, and we are confident 
that men and women are paid equally for doing the same job at the college.  We are 
working hard to address any imbalance in the workforce through inclusive and 
diverse recruitment strategies. 
 
Colin Booth CBE 
Chief Executive & Principal
 
 Headline gender pay gap figures 

  The gender pay gap is defined as the difference between the mean or median 

hourly rate of pay that male and female employees received. 

  The mean pay gap is the difference between average earnings of men and 

women.  The median pay gap is the difference between the midpoints in the 
ranges of hourly earnings of men and women.  It takes all the salaries in the 
sample lines them up in order from lowest to highest, and pick the middle-most 
salary.

 

The figures are based on hourly rates 
of pay at 30 March 2017. 
 

